001package io.cyborgcode.roa.ui.components.toggle;
002
003import io.cyborgcode.roa.ui.selenium.smart.SmartWebElement;
004import io.cyborgcode.utilities.reflections.ReflectionUtil;
005import org.openqa.selenium.By;
006
007import static io.cyborgcode.roa.ui.config.UiConfigHolder.getUiConfig;
008
009/**
010 * Provides an interface for interacting with toggle components in a UI automation
011 * framework, supporting operations to activate, deactivate, and verify toggle states.
012 * By leveraging {@link ToggleComponentType} and the {@link #DEFAULT_TYPE}, implementations
013 * can manage various toggle behaviors (e.g., switches, checkboxes) with consistent
014 * methods across different UI designs.
015 *
016 * <p>Commonly relies on Selenium-based strategies to locate and manipulate toggles
017 * identified by container elements ({@link SmartWebElement}), text, or {@link By} locators.
018 *
019 * @author Cyborg Code Syndicate üíçüë®üíª
020 */
021public interface ToggleService {
022
023   ToggleComponentType DEFAULT_TYPE = getDefaultType();
024
025   /**
026    * Retrieves the default toggle component type from the configuration.
027    *
028    * @return The default ToggleComponentType.
029    */
030   private static ToggleComponentType getDefaultType() {
031      try {
032         return ReflectionUtil.findEnumImplementationsOfInterface(ToggleComponentType.class,
033               getUiConfig().toggleDefaultType(),
034               getUiConfig().projectPackages());
035      } catch (Exception ignored) {
036         return null;
037      }
038   }
039
040   /**
041    * Activates the toggle with the specified text inside a container, using the default toggle component type.
042    *
043    * @param container  The SmartWebElement container that contains the toggle.
044    * @param toggleText The text of the toggle to activate.
045    */
046   default void activate(SmartWebElement container, String toggleText) {
047      activate(DEFAULT_TYPE, container, toggleText);
048   }
049
050   /**
051    * Activates the toggle with the specified text inside a container, using the given toggle component type.
052    *
053    * @param componentType The specific toggle component type.
054    * @param container     The SmartWebElement container that contains the toggle.
055    * @param toggleText    The text of the toggle to activate.
056    */
057   void activate(ToggleComponentType componentType, SmartWebElement container, String toggleText);
058
059   /**
060    * Activates the toggle with the specified text, using the default toggle component type.
061    *
062    * @param toggleText The text of the toggle to activate.
063    */
064   default void activate(String toggleText) {
065      activate(DEFAULT_TYPE, toggleText);
066   }
067
068   /**
069    * Activates the toggle with the specified text, using the given toggle component type.
070    *
071    * @param componentType The specific toggle component type.
072    * @param toggleText    The text of the toggle to activate.
073    */
074   void activate(ToggleComponentType componentType, String toggleText);
075
076   /**
077    * Activates the toggle identified by the specified locator, using the default toggle component type.
078    *
079    * @param toggleLocator The locator for the toggle to activate.
080    */
081   default void activate(By toggleLocator) {
082      activate(DEFAULT_TYPE, toggleLocator);
083   }
084
085   /**
086    * Activates the toggle identified by the specified locator, using the given toggle component type.
087    *
088    * @param componentType The specific toggle component type.
089    * @param toggleLocator The locator for the toggle to activate.
090    */
091   void activate(ToggleComponentType componentType, By toggleLocator);
092
093   /**
094    * Deactivates the toggle with the specified text inside a container, using the default toggle component type.
095    *
096    * @param container  The SmartWebElement container that contains the toggle.
097    * @param toggleText The text of the toggle to deactivate.
098    */
099   default void deactivate(SmartWebElement container, String toggleText) {
100      deactivate(DEFAULT_TYPE, container, toggleText);
101   }
102
103   /**
104    * Deactivates the toggle with the specified text inside a container, using the given toggle component type.
105    *
106    * @param componentType The specific toggle component type.
107    * @param container     The SmartWebElement container that contains the toggle.
108    * @param toggleText    The text of the toggle to deactivate.
109    */
110   void deactivate(ToggleComponentType componentType, SmartWebElement container, String toggleText);
111
112   /**
113    * Deactivates the toggle with the specified text, using the default toggle component type.
114    *
115    * @param toggleText The text of the toggle to deactivate.
116    */
117   default void deactivate(String toggleText) {
118      deactivate(DEFAULT_TYPE, toggleText);
119   }
120
121   /**
122    * Deactivates the toggle with the specified text, using the given toggle component type.
123    *
124    * @param componentType The specific toggle component type.
125    * @param toggleText    The text of the toggle to deactivate.
126    */
127   void deactivate(ToggleComponentType componentType, String toggleText);
128
129   /**
130    * Deactivates the toggle identified by the specified locator, using the default toggle component type.
131    *
132    * @param toggleLocator The locator for the toggle to deactivate.
133    */
134   default void deactivate(By toggleLocator) {
135      deactivate(DEFAULT_TYPE, toggleLocator);
136   }
137
138   /**
139    * Deactivates the toggle identified by the specified locator, using the given toggle component type.
140    *
141    * @param componentType The specific toggle component type.
142    * @param toggleLocator The locator for the toggle to deactivate.
143    */
144   void deactivate(ToggleComponentType componentType, By toggleLocator);
145
146   /**
147    * Checks if the toggle with the specified text inside a container is enabled, using the default toggle
148    * component type.
149    *
150    * @param container  The SmartWebElement container that contains the toggle.
151    * @param toggleText The text of the toggle to check.
152    * @return true if the toggle is enabled, false otherwise.
153    */
154   default boolean isEnabled(SmartWebElement container, String toggleText) {
155      return isEnabled(DEFAULT_TYPE, container, toggleText);
156   }
157
158   /**
159    * Checks if the toggle with the specified text inside a container is enabled, using the given toggle component type.
160    *
161    * @param componentType The specific toggle component type.
162    * @param container     The SmartWebElement container that contains the toggle.
163    * @param toggleText    The text of the toggle to check.
164    * @return true if the toggle is enabled, false otherwise.
165    */
166   boolean isEnabled(ToggleComponentType componentType, SmartWebElement container, String toggleText);
167
168   /**
169    * Checks if the toggle with the specified text is enabled, using the default toggle component type.
170    *
171    * @param toggleText The text of the toggle to check.
172    * @return true if the toggle is enabled, false otherwise.
173    */
174   default boolean isEnabled(String toggleText) {
175      return isEnabled(DEFAULT_TYPE, toggleText);
176   }
177
178   /**
179    * Checks if the toggle with the specified text is enabled, using the given toggle component type.
180    *
181    * @param componentType The specific toggle component type.
182    * @param toggleText    The text of the toggle to check.
183    * @return true if the toggle is enabled, false otherwise.
184    */
185   boolean isEnabled(ToggleComponentType componentType, String toggleText);
186
187   /**
188    * Checks if the toggle identified by the specified locator is enabled, using the default toggle component type.
189    *
190    * @param toggleLocator The locator for the toggle to check.
191    * @return true if the toggle is enabled, false otherwise.
192    */
193   default boolean isEnabled(By toggleLocator) {
194      return isEnabled(DEFAULT_TYPE, toggleLocator);
195   }
196
197   /**
198    * Checks if the toggle identified by the specified locator is enabled, using the given toggle component type.
199    *
200    * @param componentType The specific toggle component type.
201    * @param toggleLocator The locator for the toggle to check.
202    * @return true if the toggle is enabled, false otherwise.
203    */
204   boolean isEnabled(ToggleComponentType componentType, By toggleLocator);
205
206   /**
207    * Checks if the toggle with the specified text inside a container is activated, using the default toggle
208    * component type.
209    *
210    * @param container  The SmartWebElement container that contains the toggle.
211    * @param toggleText The text of the toggle to check.
212    * @return true if the toggle is activated, false otherwise.
213    */
214   default boolean isActivated(SmartWebElement container, String toggleText) {
215      return isActivated(DEFAULT_TYPE, container, toggleText);
216   }
217
218   /**
219    * Checks if the toggle with the specified text inside a container is activated, using the given toggle
220    * component type.
221    *
222    * @param componentType The specific toggle component type.
223    * @param container     The SmartWebElement container that contains the toggle.
224    * @param toggleText    The text of the toggle to check.
225    * @return true if the toggle is activated, false otherwise.
226    */
227   boolean isActivated(ToggleComponentType componentType, SmartWebElement container, String toggleText);
228
229   /**
230    * Checks if the toggle with the specified text is activated, using the default toggle component type.
231    *
232    * @param toggleText The text of the toggle to check.
233    * @return true if the toggle is activated, false otherwise.
234    */
235   default boolean isActivated(String toggleText) {
236      return isActivated(DEFAULT_TYPE, toggleText);
237   }
238
239   /**
240    * Checks if the toggle with the specified text is activated, using the given toggle component type.
241    *
242    * @param componentType The specific toggle component type.
243    * @param toggleText    The text of the toggle to check.
244    * @return true if the toggle is activated, false otherwise.
245    */
246   boolean isActivated(ToggleComponentType componentType, String toggleText);
247
248   /**
249    * Checks if the toggle identified by the specified locator is activated, using the default toggle component type.
250    *
251    * @param toggleLocator The locator for the toggle to check.
252    * @return true if the toggle is activated, false otherwise.
253    */
254   default boolean isActivated(By toggleLocator) {
255      return isActivated(DEFAULT_TYPE, toggleLocator);
256   }
257
258   /**
259    * Checks if the toggle identified by the specified locator is activated, using the given toggle component type.
260    *
261    * @param componentType The specific toggle component type.
262    * @param toggleLocator The locator for the toggle to check.
263    * @return true if the toggle is activated, false otherwise.
264    */
265   boolean isActivated(ToggleComponentType componentType, By toggleLocator);
266}
